description:
&lt;p&gt;At Benenden we are proud of our CQC outstanding rating where our patients can be assured of our excellent record in infection control and patient focussed care delivered by our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benenden Hospital is looking for a Registered Nurse to join their award winning team in the Ophthalmology unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Ophthalmology Nurse will be expected to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide the highest standards of patient-centred care; from first consultation &amp; diagnosis, on to treatment and surgery through to follow-up and discharge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work following hospital guidelines and protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and facilitate theatre lists including entering patient information on IT systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure patient care areas are safe, fit for purpose and effectively maintained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure patient information data is correctly recorded in the appropriate IT systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General supervision of junior members of the team, including providing clinical supervision/act as a mentor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will require the post holder to plan and implement the care of patients from admission through to discharge by assessing and monitoring them prior, during and after surgery. Other duties will include but is not extensive of&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing outstanding nursing interventions and care to all patients accessing the service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the safe custody of medications and controlled drugs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise the junior members of the team, including mentorship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as technical skills relevant to the role the successful applicant must be able to evidence the following :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Nurse (with supporting revalidation evidence)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Immediate Life Support training or a willingness to undertake training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong IT Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to undertake multiple tasks under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship training or a willingness to undertake training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rewards and benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Competitive salary, including an element of performance related pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- 27 days annual leave entitlement plus Bank Holidays, rising with service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Generous defined contribution pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Excellent Life Assurance benefit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free Membership of Benenden Health for Permanent Staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free parking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Subsidised eye tests&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Enhanced Maternity pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free Flu vaccinations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free tea and coffee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Subsidised on site Restaurant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Active social club&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you require further information on this role please contact Derrick Howard on 01580 857368&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Together, we work hard to maintain a safe, comfortable, patient-focused environment for the people in our care.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; All our vacancies are therefore subject to either a Standard or an Enhanced Disclosure Application to the Disclosure and Barring Service as well as satisfactory reference checks. These procedures need to be completed before a new member of staff can join the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), we have implemented a Privacy Notice to inform you, as prospective employees of Benenden Hospital Trust, of the types of data we process about you. Please visit our Careers page to read our Privacy Notice.&lt;/p&gt;
